Evidently the Red Bull Zero I have in my hands here is a pretty new phenomenon.
Having released on Jan 6 of this year, 2025, it replaced the old Red Bull Zero
in the gray can. The purpose of both the new and old Zero variants, [[like any
zero-sugar variant|Zero_Sugar_,Versus_Sugar_Free]], is to closely approximate
the taste of the original without any of the sugar. To that end, this new Red
Bull Zero uses monk fruit extract, which I had not heard of until I tried this
one. This year's [[zero-sugar Winter
Edition|Red_Bull_Winter_Edition_Iced_Vanilla_Berry_]] uses acesulfame potassium
as a sweetener instead of monk fruit; both use sucralose.

